<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6665] ZkController.publishAndWaitForDownStates should not use core name</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6665</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ZkController.publishAndWaitForDownStates uses a List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt; to keep track of all core names that have been published as down. It should use a set of coreNodeNames instead of core names for correctness.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12751161">SOLR-6665</key>
            <summary>ZkController.publishAndWaitForDownStates should not use core name</summary>
